                        <item xml:id="e1">- Däqiqä Ṣǝyon "Children of Zion" are mentioned together with the name of the donor in some supplication formulas throughout Text I-4 (fol. 12va, 18ra, 20rb etc.).&#xD;
- Omitted words inserted interlineally: fols. 3ra, 3vb, 7ra, 15ra, 28ra, 41vb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: fols. 8ra-rb, 9va, 35va, 37va, 69vb.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with thin lines: fols. 5rb, 11ra, 35va, 62ra.&#xD;
- Cues for the rubricator: fols. 35rb, 50ra, 59va.&#xD;
- Small signs written throughout Text I, in the margins; their function is not clear. &#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated passages and names left unfilled: fol. 63va-vb.&#xD;
- Scribbles and crude drawings: fols. 54vb, 59vb, 71v, 72rv.</item>
